#2620
Name A Rocky Path~
Desc A narrow and rocky path twists between larger boulders, leading up a short 
incline. Atop a small mound is a weathered keep with a watchtower, built 
from crudely hewn sandstone. A faded pennant hangs limply atop the 
watchtower, any insignia now bleached away by exposure to the elements. The 
path climbs south and ends at a pair of sturdy wooden doors, the only 
visible entrance to the structure. 
~
Sector inside~
Owner Barris~
Exit north 59018
EFlags door closed~
Exit south 2621
EFlags door closed~
End


#2621
Name Main Hall~
Desc This sizable hall represents most of the space in the keep, with smaller 
rooms to the east and south. The stone walls are partly covered by worn 
tapestries, and solid support beams of dark wood add to the impression of 
security. Except for a small bench along the west wall, the hall is empty.  
~
RoomFlags indoors~
