EFlags door closed~
End


#2623
Name Kitchen~
Desc This room may once have served as a mess hall or a kitchen, though the 
cooking implements look rather primitive. A small firepit against the west 
wall was likely used for cooking. Bare shelves adorn the other walls, and a 
solid but well-scarred table is the only noteworthy piece of furniture in 
the room. 
~
Sector inside~
Owner Barris~
Exit north 2621
Exit east 2624
Exit south 2625
End


#2624
Name Barracks~
Desc At one time, this room likely held cramped accommodations for a few 
soldiers. Rust marks on the sandstone walls indicate where bunk beds were 
securely attached. However, the bunk beds are not present now - they have 
been replaced with a larger, more comfortable bed. The large bed, unmade, is 
the only item in the room. 
~
Sector inside~
Owner Barris~
Exit north 2622
Exit west 2623
End


#2625
Name Workshop~
Desc This room is a workshop, though it doesn't seem to have seen any use 
recently. A long workbench is against the west wall, with every manner of 
tool present - hammers, chisels, sledges, tongs, files, saws, and so on. 
There is even a light anvil against the south wall, mounted on a stone 
block. Most light repair work on wood, stone or metal could be done here, 
given sufficient time. The tools are not extensive enough to do serious 
smithing or large construction projects, though. 
~
Sector inside~
Exit north 2623
Exit east 2626
EFlags door closed~
End


#2626
Name Command Post~
Desc This small but private room once served the commander of the keep. The east 
wall has a tattered and faded map of the surrounding desert posted. An old 
desk is here, stained with ancient ink and spattered with blobs of candle 
wax. A padded chair, clearly much newer, is behind the desk, while a lantern 
provides a warm illumination to the room. 
~
Sector inside~
Owner Barris~
Exit west 2625
EFlags door closed~
End


