#2628
Name Watchtower~
Desc Above the rest of the keep, this tower chamber has small windows to allow 
the occupants to look out in all directions. An iron ladder on the north 
wall allows both ascent to the tower roof and descent to the base of the 
tower. There are hooks on the walls, but whatever implements they held are 
long since gone. A small table is in the center of this room, with a few 
rickety looking chairs surrounding it. 
~
Sector inside~
Exit up 2629
Exit down 2622
End


#2629
Name Top of a Watchtower~
Desc Under the open sky, the roof of the watchtower allows an excellent view of 
the surrounding desert in all directions. Crumbling crenellations reach 
about waist high, and prevent the careless from falling. In the northeast 
corner of the roof, a pennant hangs from a slightly rusted iron pole. The 
banner was once blue, but is too tattered and faded from exposure to bear a 
recognizable emblem. 
~
